Helicopter scrambled in search for manA POLICE helicopter was scrambled to find a man in East Renfrewshire.The air support unit was drafted in during a search of Thornliebank, Rouken Glen and Newton Mearns on Wednesday afternoon.Police said a search was launched to &quot;trace a man in the area&quot;.No further details of the incident were available.The helicopter was seen circling above local roads, including Orchard Park Avenue, Rouken Glen Road and Stewarton Road.